latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Be your most beautiful self, inside and out. 
What makes YOU feel beautiful? 🤍✨
-
Skincare has helped change my skin tremendously. I never used to care for having an effective skincare regimen or took time to love my skin. After seeing the beautiful changes in my skin, I love the glow my skin gives off. I love @aliciakeys new skincare brand @keyssoulcare, because of the many amazing meanings behind her brand. After using Keys Soulcare products, it reminded me to give myself the space and time to self-care. To slow down and nurture my body/mind/skin. All of the products are incredibly and beautifully made. Keys Soulcare products are clean, safe, and cruelty-free. They include skin nourishing ingredients like Manuka honey, malachite, and hojicha powder to create effective formulas gentle enough for all skin types. 🌿🌞🌊

latestPosts.caption:
This is a Navajo cradleboard, something I’ve used with my baby since she was a newborn. She’s 6 months now and still sleeps in it every day—naps and bedtime. It’s been a huge help for us because she sleeps longer and more peacefully, without rolling around or waking herself up. 

In Indigenous families, cradleboards are a traditional baby carrier and sleep tool. They’re made to support the baby’s posture and help them feel secure, kind of like being swaddled. The firm board behind them is usually made of wood and keeps them upright and protected, while soft ties keep them gently wrapped in place.

It’s something I grew up seeing, but now that I use one with my own child, I see why it’s stayed around for generations. It works—and it’s portable, safe, and comforting for babies. It’s also a reminder that a lot of our old ways still fit into modern parenting. 🤍🪶🪽🧸 

#navajo #indigenous #navajomom #native #cradleboard

Tulane surprised me with the most beautiful and meaningful graduation and Mother’s Day gift I could’ve asked for — and I’m still emotional about it. 🥹✨

He picked out three stunning necklaces from Caitlyn Minimalist, and each one holds such a special place in my heart. Two necklaces have both of our daughters’ names — Seeley and Tinley — delicately engraved. Another piece features our birthstones side by side, symbolizing the life we’ve built together.

Every detail is so thoughtful and personal, and I truly feel so loved and seen. I can’t wait to layer them all together and wear this reminder of my little family close to my heart every day. 💕 Thank you, Tulane — and thank you @caitlynminimalist for creating such timeless, sentimental pieces. 

#CaitlynMinimalist #Jewelry #MothersDayGifts

latestPosts.caption:
I did it! I graduated with a degree in science! 🎓🧬🧫🧪🥼

I pushed through the toughest season of my life—pregnant, overwhelmed, and so close to giving up. Postpartum hit hard, and there were so many nights I wanted to drop everything. But I kept going… because of my babies, and because of the love and support I had surrounding me.

I finished my classes just 3 weeks postpartum, taking proctored final exams while breastfeeding Tinley and holding her the entire time. I stayed up studying until 4am while everyone slept, then woke up at 6am with Tinley and did it all over again. This last semester was no joke—late nights, exhaustion, and sacrifices—but I FINISHED STRONG.

A huge shoutout to my love—for believing in me, encouraging me, and helping me push through even when I was ready to quit. I couldn’t have done this without you. 🩷

To my mom, dad, and brother—thank you for always showing up for me. Every single time, without hesitation. Your support has meant the world.

To my grandma and aunt—thank you for driving out to every single event no matter the distance. From Tinley’s baby shower to her first laugh, Seeley’s birthday to my graduation—you show what true family looks like. You always make it happen.

And to my little family—thank you. Seeley, you’ve always been my reason to dream bigger. And now with Tinley, doing this journey with both of you by my side has made me prouder than I could ever put into words. Thank you to my love for making it possible for me to be the present mom I always wanted to be, while still chasing my goals.

We did it—for them, for us, and for every mama chasing her dreams through the chaos.

#Graduated #AssociateInScience #MomLife #Postpartum #IndigenousAndEducated #Graduate #SAHM #SecondTimeMom #MomAndDad
